## ğŸ› ï¸ Installation & Deployment

### Method 1: Direct Vercel Deployment

1. **Download all files** from this repository
2. **Create a new project** on [Vercel](https://vercel.com)
3. **Drag and drop** the entire folder to Vercel dashboard
4. **Wait for deployment** - Your site will be live automatically

### Method 2: GitHub + Vercel

1. **Create a new GitHub repository**
2. **Upload all files** to the repository
3. **Connect your GitHub** to Vercel
4. **Import the repository** and deploy

### Method 3: Local Development

```bash
# Clone or download the project
cd hacker-portfolio

# Start local server (Python)
python -m http.server 3000

# Or using Node.js
npx serve .
```

Then visit `http://localhost:3000`

## âš™ï¸ Configuration

### Customize Telegram Channels

Edit `index.html` in the Telegram Channels section:

```html
<div class="telegram-item">
    <h3><i class="fab fa-telegram"></i> Your Channel Name</h3>
    <p>Channel description here</p>
    <a href="https://t.me/yourchannel" class="btn" target="_blank">Join Channel</a>
</div>
```

### Update Contact Information

Modify the contact section in `index.html`:

```html
<a href="https://t.me/yourusername" class="btn" target="_blank">
    <i class="fab fa-telegram"></i> Telegram
</a>
<a href="mailto:your@email.com" class="btn">
    <i class="fas fa-envelope"></i> Email
</a>
```

### Change Color Scheme

Edit CSS variables in `styles/globals.css`:

```css
:root {
    --primary-color: #00ff00;  /* Green terminal text */
    --background-color: #0a0a0a; /* Dark background */
    --accent-color: #0088cc;   /* Telegram blue */
}
```

